OL,3,CSickness benefits bill 'devastating',
OL,4,CStarmer says as he defends reforms
OL,6,FWriting in The Times newspaper, Sir
OL,7,FKeir pointed to the 2.8 million
OL,8,Fworking age people out of work due to
OL,9,Flong-term sickness, claiming this was
OL,10,Fa "damning indictment of the
OL,11,FConservative record" on welfare.
OL,13,FThe Prime Minister added: "The result
OL,14,Fis devastating for the public
OL,15,Ffinances. By 2030 we are projected to
OL,16,Fspend #70 billion a year on working-
OL,17,Fage incapacity and disability benefits
OL,18,Falone.
