OL,3,CSickness benefits bill 'devastating',
OL,4,CStarmer says as he defends reforms
OL,6,F` Legislating for a so-called "right
OL,7,Fto try", which Work and Pensions
OL,8,FSecretary Liz Kendall said would
OL,9,Fensure people are able to "take the
OL,10,Fplunge and try work ` without the fear
OL,11,Fthis will put their benefits at risk".
OL,13,FAs part of its reforms, the Government
OL,14,Falso said it will invest an additional
OL,15,F#1 billion a year by 2029/2030 to help
OL,16,Fsupport people into work, including
OL,17,Fthrough one-to-one help.
OL,19,FThe announcement was met with
OL,20,Fcriticism from Labour backbenchers,
OL,21,Funions and charities.
